  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### What's your issue about?\r\nContract Interfaces are an extension to an `address`, so it should have most (if not all) of the `address` members:\r\n* `address.balance`\r\n* `address.codehash`\r\n* `address.codesize`\r\n* `address.is_contract`\r\n\r\nError:\r\n```python\r\ninterface PiggyBank:\r\n    def deposit(): payable\r\n\r\npiggy: PiggyBank\r\n\r\n@public\r\ndef foo() -> uint256:\r\n    self.piggy.deposit()\r\n    return self.piggy.balance  \r\n```\r\n```\r\nE       vyper.exceptions.UnknownAttribute: PiggyBank has no member 'balance'                                                             \r\nE       function 'foo', line 10:11                                                                                                       \r\nE             9     self.piggy.deposit()                                                                                                 \r\nE       ---> 10     return self.piggy.balance                                                                                            \r\nE       -------------------^                                                                                                             \r\nE            11       \r\n```\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed?\r\nI believe `assert address.is_contract` is inserted prior to any external call to the interface, so clearly it is useful. I think it's best that this automatic check continues to exist only on call (and not on assignment, as this precludes counterfactual instantiations), so no change required there, but someone might want to add additional checks after assignment, for example:\r\n```python\r\npiggy: PiggyBank = PiggyBank(piggy_address)\r\nassert piggy.is_contract\r\n# OR\r\nassert piggy.codehash == self.expected_piggy_codehash\r\n# OR\r\nassert piggy.codesize == 42  # Well, maybe not this one as much\r\n```\r\nI know it's just as easy to perform these checks prior to assignment (and probably more advisible to do so), but it just seems inconsistent not to have access to the `address` API for interfaces",
